  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening the Capacity to Reduce Environmental Impacts of Displacement in the Pacific</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, IOM is developing and promoting a multi-media training module in collaboration with the United Nations Environment Programme (UNEP) to ensure government actors understand the importance of incorporating environmental concerns and solutions into displacement management across the Pacific region. IOM and UNEP are working directly with government actors in Vanuatu, as well as promoting peer-to peer learning with government actors from Fiji and the Solomon Islands.</narrative>
  </description>
